      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CROYDON (2) is a consistent dog overall, in the frame at six of 31 starts including 19 wins but missed the frame latest when fifth (30.78) over 525m at this track. Form at the trip excellent including seven wins. Looks well placed here and should prove hard to beat again. ZIPPING FIYERO (3) goes very well at the course with two wins and a placing from four starts. Scored by 6 lengths last time (29.68) in a Grade 5 over 525m at this track. Can feature in the finish. KEEP ROLLING (7) is a progressive type who recorded his 13th career win last time out (29.53) at Sandown. Has a good record here including four wins. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. NIGHTTIME (1) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 1.5 lengths third (29.82) in a Grade 4 at Sandown.",
